POLICE detectives in Enugu have arrested a 75-year-old man for allegedly defiling a 5-year-old girl in the bush. The suspect whose name was given as Moses Eze hails from Azuebo village in Eha-Ndiagu, Eha-Alumona in Nsukka Local Government Area of Enugu State. The septuagenarian is now with the operatives of the state Criminal Investigations Department (CID) in Enugu over his alleged involvement in the defilement of the five-year-old girl. Tribunal nullifies PDP lawmaker’s election in Oyo,… Tribunal dismisses three petitions, affirms Ihedioha’s… We’ll make Nigeria’s GDP largest in Sub-Saharan… Fire guts WHO storage facility in Osogbo ALSO READ: Gov Bello describes Okene-Lokoja road ‘an eyesore,’ calls for FG’s intervention Confirming the story, the State Police Public Relations Officer, Ebere Amarizu, on Saturday said, “the suspect  defiled a five-year-old girl identified as one Ogechukwu  Olowu  after allegedly luring his victim to the bush” Amarizu further said, “the victim’s mother had sent her on an errand on that fateful day with  her friend whom the suspect equally dispatched to go and buy something before embarking on the act” The Commissioner of Police, Ahmad Abdurrahman, the Police Spokesman said, had directed for a full-scale investigation into the unfortunate incident while the suspect is helping the operatives in their investigations. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
